Software verification and correctness

We aim to build on the existing strengths within=20
the Mathematical Foundations group in the=20
Department of Computer Science. The group=20
comprises Prof Guy McCusker and Dr Jim Laird=20
(semantics), Dr Alessio Guglielmi (proof theory),=20
Dr John Power (category theory) and Prof James=20
Davenport (computer algebra).

We seek to strengthen its activities via the=20
appointment of a Prize Fellow in software=20
verification & correctness, to be understood=20
broadly, to complement existing expertise; it=20
would also be desirable to strengthen connections=20
with other groups in the department, particularly=20
with Dr Marina De Vos and Dr Julian Padget in the=20
Intelligent Systems group. The Fellow would be=20
coming into a well-resourced, lively group that=20
runs a weekly seminar series, which once a month=20
is jointly held with Swansea's Proofs, Complexity=20
and Verification seminar.

The Math Foundations group belongs to the Wessex=20
Theory Seminar, comprising the Computer Science=20
Departments of Bath, Oxford, Southampton,=20
Cambridge, Imperial College, Queen Mary, Sussex=20
and Swansea. The group has a good track record of=20
nurturing early career researchers.

=46or informal inquiries contact Prof Guy McCusker: G.A.McCusker AT bath.ac.=
uk

