Prize Fellow - Department of Computer Science
Salary:   Starting from =A337,012, rising to =A344,166
Closing Date:   Monday 21 May 2012
Interview Date:   See advert
Reference:  JK1000

To further enhance our academic base, we are=20
making a strategic investment in recruiting=20
University of Bath Prize Fellows across all=20
disciplines.

This is an opportunity for outstanding=20
post-doctoral researchers to develop their=20
academic career in a supportive and=20
well-resourced research environment.

In the Faculty of Science we will appoint a total=20
of six Fellows to further strengthen and develop=20
areas of existing research excellence.

In the Department of Computer Science we invite applications in the areas of=
:

* Machine Learning
* Software Verification and Correctness
* Modelling Behaviour Transmission

Details of these priority areas and the=20
=46aculty-wide appointment process can be found=20
here:=20
<http://www.bath.ac.uk/science/prize-fellows>.

The Fellows will be expected to pursue an=20
independent programme of research, including=20
publishing in top quality journals and securing=20
external research grants.

The initial appointment will be to a fixed-term=20
Research Fellow post with the expectation of=20
transfer to a permanent lectureship at the end of=20
year two, or exceptionally at the end of year=20
three.

Applicants should upload a CV and a 2-page=20
outline of their research plans over the next 3-5=20
years, showing how these complement and enhance=20
existing research within the relevant priority=20
area.

Interviews will take place on Friday 29th June or Monday 2nd July 2012


